        <section xml:id="sec-equally-likely">
          <title>Equally Likely Outcomes</title>
          <p>
            Let us begin with a fairly simple situation and try to 
            understand how our intuition might (possibly) rightly 
            direct us. Suppose five friends want to decide who
            should pick the next book for their book club. Because
            they are all too polite to insist, Ali suggests they put
            their names on five identical slips of paper, put those
            slips of paper into a container. We will imagine that
            container as a 
            metal urn out of a gentle respect for mathematical 
            tradition. Ben, Cal, Dani, Eve all agree to this system.
            In part this is based on their shared intuition that
            each of them are equally likely to be chosen by this
            method. This is an important assumption, and is one that
            we would do well to keep in mind for future situations 
            as well.
          </p>
          <example>
            <title>Randomly Selecting One Object From Five</title>
